      <body>
        <div>
            <pb facs="#TL-0561.jpg" n="part4_p087.jpg" xml:id="img_0087" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part4_p087.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_87_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>dʼavoir lʼétat de
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>-56-
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>expression of this feeling. But it also shows the demonstration. Now perhaps some consistent
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>thinkers among you will ask, "Why not, if we make an exception anyhow in terms of the
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>Christ, why
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>not in terms also of the Vicar of Christ? If the principle of the existential
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>more cases?” This is
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_2_tl_10" n="N010"/>situation with respect to truth is broken in the one case, why not in
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_2_tl_11" n="N011"/>the
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_87_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>a very valid argument, and the only answer can be that it is necessary to draw consequence of the
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>Protestant principle and say that even JESUS is not an ultimate authority, but that AS THE
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>CHRIST, he is the plaw Reality. It is always impossible to drive, from the words of Jesus,
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>authoritarian statements which claim to be infallible. It is first impossible because the problem of
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>interpretation comes and all the relativities then hidethemselves in the form of interpretation. And
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>secondly it is impossible because it is more honest to acknowledge that Jesus is not an infallible
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>teacher but that He is the bearer of the New Reality, of the Spirit, and the Spirit is not an
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_3_tl_8" n="N008"/>infallibleteacher but a creative interpreter who guide into all truth.
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_3_tl_9" n="N009"/>Now if this is seen, then we can accept the consistency of the Roman Church and are
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_3_tl_10" n="N010"/>at the same time radically aware of the fact that neither the Vicar of Christ, nor Jesus in His
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_3_tl_11" n="N011"/>words, can be called an authority in principle.
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_87_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>If this is not the case, we come into the situation of the Roman Church, where a
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>bondage occurs, even for the Cope. This bondage are the prior decisions of the Church, in Councils
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>and decisions ex cathedra by the Pope. Now these prior decisions are called, in the dogmatic Beology
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>of the Roman Church, DE FIDE, meaning they are matters "of faith"—and "faith" here means:
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>dʼun autre
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>de votre beau et
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>lʼauteur sommée de
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>dʼune manière beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>cʼest un
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>de ses
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>cʼest en lʼautre
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_13" n="N013"/>dʼun autre
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_14" n="N014"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_15" n="N015"/>dans le
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_16" n="N016"/>dʼadresse à
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_17" n="N017"/>dʼune manière
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_18" n="N018"/>dʼune manière
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_19" n="N019"/>toutes
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_20" n="N020"/>M r de
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_21" n="N021"/>dʼun autre
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_22" n="N022"/>Monsieur Mounard, et elle est vrai que
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_23" n="N023"/>dʼoù il y a e
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_24" n="N024"/>toutes
               <lb facs="#facs_87_tr_1_tl_25" n="N025"/>de votre beau et très-dire
            </p>
            
